			  	What &quot;updated guide&quot; are you referring to?<br />
The link on the homepage for &quot;New Archspace Manual&quot; had the text I used in my original post.<br />
<br />
To your point about &quot;Planet investment costs are halved&quot;: How is this mathmatically proven, the numbers I've previously posted show there is no differnece.<br />
<br />
To your point about &quot;Maximum Research investment is doubled&quot;: I offer the below numbers which show a 5% gain from 176 to 187.<br />
<br />
On my Domestic screen the Research Point is at 176. <br />
The Research page states the Max PP Usage per Turn is 220.<br />
The turn summary states that the RP Change was 187 RP.<br />
<br />
There is gain of 11 RP vs. 220 over the 176. <br />
<br />
I picked a tech to research next and the total was 12,566 on one turn and the next turn it was 12,753 for a difference of 187.<br />
<br />
So I only see 11 of the 220 being used vs. doubling which would be 440.			   <P align=right></P>
